---

## 1️⃣ Show Databases

// Displays all databases available in MongoDB

**Syntax:**
show dbs

**Example:**
show dbs
// Shows all available databases → admin, config, local

---

## 2️⃣ Use Database

// Switches to a specific database (creates if not exists)

**Syntax:**
use <dbname>

**Example:**
use studentDB
// Switches to studentDB (creates it if it does not exist)

---

## 3️⃣ Create Collection

// Creates a new collection inside the current database

**Syntax:**
db.createCollection("<name>")

**Example:**
db.createCollection("students")
// Creates a new collection named "students"

---

## 4️⃣ Drop Database

// Deletes the currently selected database permanently

**Syntax:**
db.dropDatabase()

**Example:**
db.dropDatabase()
// Deletes the current database in use

---

## 5️⃣ Show Collections

// Displays all collections present in the current database

**Syntax:**
show collections

**Example:**
show collections
// Lists all collections in the current DB → students, teachers

---

## 6️⃣ Drop Collection

// Removes a specific collection from the current database

**Syntax:**
db.<collection>.drop()

**Example:**
db.students.drop()
// Deletes the "students" collection

---

## 7️⃣ Insert One Document

// Inserts a single record/document into a collection

**Syntax:**
db.<collection>.insertOne({ key: value })

**Example:**
db.students.insertOne({ name: "Rahul", age: 22 })
// Inserts one student record into "students" collection

---

## 8️⃣ Insert Many Documents

// Inserts multiple records/documents at once into a collection

**Syntax:**
db.<collection>.insertMany(\[{...}, {...}])

**Example:**
db.students.insertMany(\[
{ name: "Shreyas", age: 21 },
{ name: "Amit", age: 21 }
])
// Inserts multiple student records in one go

---

## 9️⃣ Find Documents

// Retrieves one or more documents from a collection

**Syntax:**
db.<collection>.find()

**Example:**
db.students.find()
// Retrieves all documents inside "students"

---
